=\"fn\">a</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Init/WF.html#Acc.ndrec","kind":"def","line":32,"name":"Acc.ndrec","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/9d4ad1273f6cea397c3066c2c83062a4410d16bf/src/Init/WF.lean#L32-L35"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/WF.html#Acc.intro\"><span class=\"name\">Acc</span>.<span class=\"name\">intro</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Sort</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">r</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">y</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">r</span> <span class=\"fn\">y</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/WF.html#Acc\">Acc</a> <span class=\"fn\">r</span> <span class=\"fn\">y</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/WF.html#Acc\">Acc</a> <span class=\"fn\">r</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A value is accessible if for all `y` such that `r y x`, `y` is also accessible.\nNote that if there exists no `y` such that `r y x`, then `x` is accessible. Such an `x` is called a\n_base case_.\n","docLink":"./Init/WF.html#Acc.intro","kind":"ctor","line":25,"name":"Acc.intro","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/9d4ad1273f6cea397c3066c2c83062a4410d16bf/src/Init/WF.lean#L25-L30"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">inductive</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/WF.html#Acc\"><span class=\"name\">Acc</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Sort</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">r</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`Acc` is the accessibility predicate. Given some relation `r` (e.g. `<`) and a value `x`,\n`Acc r x` means that `x` is accessible through `r`:\n\n`x` is accessible if there exists no infinite sequence `... < y₂ < y₁ < y₀ < x`.\n","docLink":"./Init/WF.html#Acc","kind":"inductive","line":18,"name":"Acc","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/9d4ad1273f6cea397c3066c2c83062a4410d16bf/src/Init/WF.lean#L18-L30"}}],"imports":["Init.BinderNameHint","Init.Data.Nat.Basic"],"instances":[{"className":"WellFoundedRelation","name":"sizeOfWFRel","typeNames":[]},{"className":"Decidable","name":"Prod.Lex.instDecidableRelOfDecidableEq","typeNames":["Prod.Lex"]},{"className":"WellFoundedRelation","name":"Prod.instWellFoundedRelation","typeNames":["Prod"]},{"className":"WellFoundedRelation","name":"PSigma.instWellFoundedRelation","typeNames":["PSigma"]}],"name":"Init.WF"}